    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>

                <p>This weekly only I received <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                        Lowâ€™s</persName>
                    <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0058">book</title></bibl>. The little I
                    have been able to read of them gives me much satisfaction. By spring I can
                    thoroughly peruse them. Be so good as to transmit the inclosed by first post;
                    &amp; y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> set of <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0231">Flora scotica</title></bibl> which you will give yrself the
                    trouble of replacing with another by means of the inclosed. I thank you kindly
                    for the rare map &amp; the two heads, all which I value as proofs of y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> friendship.</p>
                <p><persName ref="pe0226">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Panton</persName> called on
                    me the other day &amp; desired his best complimts. He is now gone to <placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName>, with such a thirst of knowledge as must
                    distinguish him.</p>
                <p>Be so kind as to present my compliments to <persName ref="pe0226">D<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi> Ramsay</persName> &amp; beg he w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> fill up the directions to <persName ref="pe0023">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Stuart</persName>, that it may reach him
                    speedily.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am Dear Sir <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> most obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Thomas Pennant.</persName></signed>
                    <dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> Nov<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                            7<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1777.</dateline></closer>

                <postscript>
                    <p>I hope you will as much credit as it deserves to a malignant libel against me
                        in one of the papers. Be assured when I gave <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0017">the great Br. Zoology</title></bibl> to the Welsh school, I
                        cleared it of above 70<hi rend="superscript">L</hi> debt out of my own
                        pocket. &amp; all that I got for the little editions were a few copies which
                        I gave away and 100<hi rend="superscript">L</hi> which I presented the
                        school with on March 1. 1775.</p>
                    <p>As to <persName ref="pe0139">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                            Lightfoot</persName>, his book cost me 400L: &amp; I have secured to him
                        the entire profits.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
